# Memory Optimizations
CONFIG_PYTORCH_CUDA_ALLOC_CONF="expandable_segments:True"

# Test execution
CONFIG_TEST_PARALLEL_JOBS=1
CONFIG_OUTPUT_DIR="test_matrix_results_kv_pruning"

# Ablation step details:
#
# BASELINE - Step V0
# ==================
# - Step V0: Pure baseline GPT-2
#   Architecture: Standard SDPA attention, standard MLP
#   Purpose: Baseline reference for all comparisons
#
# DELAYED ACTIVATION - Steps V11-V13
# ===================================
# All use 75-step warmup before enabling reciprocal mechanisms
# Based on ra-mean.png observation: w_rec drops before step 75
#
# - Step V11: R-MLP basic with delayed activation
#   Architecture: R_ff=64 (ratio 47:1), delayed start at step 75
#   Purpose: Simple R-MLP baseline with warmup
#
# - Step V12: Unified RA with delayed activation
#   Architecture: R=4, delayed start at step 75
#   Purpose: Test if RA benefits from established features first
#
# - Step V13: R-MLP golden ratio with delayed activation
#   Architecture: R_ff=1152 (ratio 1.67:1, near φ=1.618), delayed at 75
#   Purpose: Test if balanced MLP split needs warmup
#
# KV CACHE PRUNING - Steps V14-V15
# =================================
# Test memory reduction via attention token pruning
#
# - Step V14: V11 + KV pruning (golden ratio)
#   Base: R-MLP basic delayed (V11)
#   KV pruning: Fixed k=391 of 1024 tokens (38.2% kept)
#   Strategy: Top-327 by score + Last-64 recency buffer
#   Memory: 61.8% reduction (1,572,864 → 600,576 elements per layer)
#   Purpose: Test if golden ratio pruning maintains quality
#
# - Step V15: V13 + KV pruning (learned ratio)
#   Base: R-MLP golden delayed (V13)
#   KV pruning: Learnable keep_ratio (init 0.382)
#   Strategy: Model learns optimal k vs fixed golden ratio
#   Constraints: ratio ∈ [0.05, 1.0], minimum k=64 tokens
#   Purpose: Discover if learned ratio > fixed ratio
#
# Expected comparisons:
# - V11 vs V0: Does basic R-MLP + delayed help?
# - V12 vs V0: Does delayed RA help?
# - V13 vs V11: Does golden ratio R-MLP > basic R-MLP?
# - V14 vs V11: Quality loss from 61.8% KV cache reduction?
# - V15 vs V14: Does learned ratio > fixed golden ratio?
#
# Usage:
# 1. Full ablation (2 hours/step, 12 hours total for 6 steps):
#    make defconfig-gpt2-kv-pruning-ablation && make
#
# 2. Quick sanity check (60 seconds/step):
#    make defconfig-gpt2-kv-pruning-ablation
#    GPT2_MAX_TIME=60 make
#
# 3. Dry-run validation (CPU, ~60 seconds total):
#    make defconfig-gpt2-kv-pruning-ablation
#    make check
